
Install JDK

Download JDK:

Go to Oracle or AdoptOpenJDK.

Download the appropriate JDK version for your operating system.


Install JDK:

Run the installer and follow the prompts.


Set Up Environment Variables:

On Windows:

1. Set JAVA_HOME to your JDK installation path.


2. Add JAVA_HOME\bin to the system's PATH variable.



On macOS/Linux: Add the following to your shell configuration file (.bashrc, .zshrc, etc.):

export JAVA_HOME=/path/to/jdk
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH


Verify Installation: Run the following command in your terminal:

java -version
javac -version
